  "texts": [
    "Here's an example of how this might look: as a child is engaged in a writing task, rather than make autocorrections, the system could highlight mistakes, drawing the child's attention, and suggesting helpful resources for self-correction (Warschauer et al., 2023).",
    "In this way, LLMs, as material cognitive prosthetics, could be adopted to \"provide new interactive possibilities for moving forward to learn new [skills]\" (Malafouris, 2021. Pp. 50).",
    "In this paper we have suggested that it may be fruitful to approach education as a process whose aim is to nudge embodied interactive agents along empowering dynamics of prediction error minimisation.",
    "Understanding education in this way also revealed, at least in outline, some of the ways essentially embodied, active beings such as ourselves might learn to make better use of new resources such as those of generative AI.",
    "To this end we have adopted the AIF (sec."
  ]
